body:
There is a Yosys bug in parsing empty positional args. They are simply ignored (skipped).

E.g. the following code produces an error for mismatching port directionalities when processed with `prep -flatten`:

```
module demo(input a, output y);
  demo_sub sub (y, , 1'b1, a);
endmodule

module demo_sub(output y, z, input a, b);
  assign y = a & b, z = a | b;
endmodule
```

